Message.MsgText: WADM9251E=WADM9251E: Parameters are specified on command step {0} but the command step target is set to "false".
Message.Explanation: Because the value of the command step target is "false", the step cannot be performed. However, step parameters have been specified, which indicate an intent to perform the step.
Message.UserResponse: If you want to perform the command step, specify the command step target to the value "true", or specify no command step target.

Message.MsgText: WADM0043E=WADM0043E: The Web server name {0} is invalid. Only alphanumeric characters are allowed.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the Web server name to allow alphanumeric characters only.

Message.MsgText: WADM0046E=WADM0046E: Platform mismatch. Hostname {0} on specified platform {1} matches existing node {2}, but node {2} platform type is {3}. Please specify a consistent platform.
Message.Explanation: A host name must specify the same platform type of the matched existing node.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a matching platform type when the host name matches an existing node.

Message.Explanation: Test message - these are the new message numbers for future messages

Message.MsgText: WADM0042E=WADM0042E: Admin server port integer {0} is not valid. Out of bounds.
Message.Explanation: The port number for the IBM Administration must be an integer between 1 and 65536.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the port to be an integer between 1 and 65536. The default value is 8008.

Message.MsgText: WADM0045E=WADM0045E: Web server {0} already exists. Only one Web server can be defined for WebSphere Express. Web server {1} is deleted.
Message.Explanation: One Web server definition is supported for WebSphere Application Server - Express.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the existing Web server or delete the existing Web server and create a new Web server defintion.

Message.MsgText: WADM0048E=WADM0048E: Web server install path {0} is not valid for a node on {1} platform. Web server path must be fully qualified.
Message.Explanation: The installation path name for the Web server is not fully qualified.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a fully qualified installation path for the Web server.

Message.MsgText: WADM0041E=WADM0041E: Web server port integer {0} is not valid. Out of bounds.
Message.Explanation: The Web server port must be an integer between 1 and 65536.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the port to be an integer between 1 and 65536.

Message.MsgText: WADM0044E=WADM0044E: ServiceName is required property for IBM HTTP Server on Windows.
Message.Explanation: The ServiceName property is used during the administration process for the IBM HTTP Server on Windows. This ServiceName property is created during the Web server installation process. For example IBMHTTPServerx.x.
Message.UserResponse: Specify the ServiceName that was create for IBM HTTP Server when the Web server was installed.

Message.MsgText: WADM0047E=WADM0047E: Configuration file {0} is not valid for a node on {1} platform. Configuration file must be fully qualified.
Message.Explanation: The configuration file name is not fully qualified.
Message.UserResponse: Specify a fully qualified configuration file name
